## Design System Rules

### ‚úÖ Always Use Tokens

- **Colors**: Role tokens (`--brand`, `--surface`) not raw hex
- **Spacing**: Scale tokens (`--space-6`) not ad-hoc px values
- **Typography**: Size tokens (`--text-lg`) not hardcoded sizes
- **Radii**: Preset tokens (`--r-md`) not custom values

### üö´ Never Do This

```css
/* ‚ùå Hardcoded values */
.component {
  color: #9D6B7B;
  padding: 24px 18px;
  font-size: 16px;
  border-radius: 8px;
}
```

### ‚úÖ Always Do This

```css
/* ‚úÖ Token-driven */
.component {
  color: var(--brand);
  padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4);
  font-size: var(--text-md);
  border-radius: var(--r-md);
}
```

---

## Testing Themes

Use the **theme toggle** (sun/moon icons) in the Storybook toolbar to test components in both light and dark modes.

All role tokens automatically adapt:
- `--bg` switches from light to dark background
- `--fg` switches from dark to light foreground
- `--surface` adjusts contrast appropriately
- Brand colors maintain accessibility in both modes

